'''Love''' is a basic dimension of [[human]] experience that is variously conveyed as a sense of tender [[affection]], an intense [[interpersonal attraction|attraction]], the foundation of [[intimacy]] and good [[interpersonal chemistry]], willing self-sacrifice on behalf of another, and as an [[ineffability|ineffable]] sense of affinity or connection to nature, other living beings, or even that which is unseen. '''Love''' is a basic dimension of [[human]] experience that is variously conveyed as a sense of tender [[affection]], an intense [[interpersonal attraction|attraction]], the foundation of [[intimacy]] and good [[interpersonal chemistry]], willing self-sacrifice on behalf of another, and as an [[ineffability|ineffable]] sense of affinity or connection to nature, other living beings, or even that which is unseen. It manifests itself in [[feeling]]s, [[emotion]], [[behavior]], [[thoughts]], [[perception]] and [[Attitude (psychology)|attitude]].
